  "title": "INSTRUMENTATION TECHNICIAN",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles & Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><li>Conduct preventive maintenance and regular inspections of instrumentation equipment<strong>, </strong>as well as assist in troubleshooting/failure analysis to identify/highlight any rectification work required</li><li>Perform repairs and modification works including operating and maintaining all instrumentation and equipment as assigned under routine/preventive maintenance programme</li><li>Calibrate and test instruments to ensure accuracy and functionality.</li><li>Provide support and services in addressing any plant/equipment maintenance issues that may arise after office hours in order to minimise disruption/downtime to plant/equipment operation.</li><li>Ensure that all HSE and Safe Work Procedure (SWP) are followed</li></li></ul>",
